1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

ATLAS-220 represents the flagship conceptual humanoid biomechanical architecture developed by Parallel Industries 220.

The project establishes a unified engineering platform integrating intelligent robotics, electro-hydraulic actuation, artificial musculature, distributed sensing and modular system engineering into a scalable architecture designed for future generations of human-centered robotic systems.

Rather than representing a single robot, ATLAS-220 defines an engineering ecosystem capable of supporting multiple robotic platforms through standardized interfaces, modular subsystems and common engineering principles.

The architecture has been conceived to maximize maintainability, adaptability, reliability and future scalability while providing a common technological foundation for future PI220 robotic developments.

All concepts contained within this dossier represent conceptual engineering work intended for laboratory investigation, computational analysis and prototype validation.

