11. ENGINEERING CONCLUSIONS

ATLAS-220 establishes a standardized conceptual architecture for the development of future biomechanical robotic systems within the Parallel Industries 220 ecosystem.

The architecture integrates structural engineering, electro-hydraulic motion, artificial musculature, distributed sensing, onboard artificial intelligence and modular energy systems into a unified research framework.

Its modular organization is intended to simplify manufacturing, maintenance, technology upgrades and long-term system evolution while providing a common engineering foundation for future robotic platforms.

All engineering assumptions, conceptual assessments and projected capabilities described in this dossier require computational analysis, laboratory experimentation and prototype validation before operational performance claims can be established.

